                <h2>The "Density Illusion" provided by Oils</h2>

                <p>While an organic oil cannot create a new hair follicle, it can be mathematically manipulated to create the <em>optical illusion</em> of a thicker beard. When you coat a very thin, wispy "vellus" hair with an incredibly heavy, sticky oil like pure Castor Oil, you physically increase the diameter of that tiny hair strand by wrapping it in a microscopic sheath of lipid.</p>
                <p>When you have 500 wispy thin hairs, and you suddenly coat all 500 of them in heavy Castor Oil, the entire structural density of the beard appears drastically thicker in the mirror. It is a temporary mechanical trick, but it is highly effective while you endure the awkward phase of growth.</p>

